Dia lupa, rakyat kecil cuma di bodohi, katanya lah itu mereka jg jadi pekerja disana bagus. Padahal cuma kurun waktu berapa bulan aja dan berapa tahun, sisanya mereka rakyat yg awam kembali ke kampungnya, akhirnya back to nature ga ada kerjaan lagi. *Moving the district capital (IKK) alone on Java Island takes a very long time. In East Java Province, there are 7 that have moved IKK. author: @bfourtys
comment:
Ikn klo saya bilang adalah blunder besar nya jokowi dari total 10thn masa kerja nya. 

Apa kita akan memvonis jokowi gagal dalam kerja nya dan ngehujat nya di waktu yg akan datang ?

Saya sih tetep mengapresiasi kerja jokowi dan tetep menganggap presiden terbaik di dalam mempercepat pembangunan infrastruktur di seluruh negara ini. Kita baliik kan ke diri kita klo kita di posisi nya jokowi, jd pemimpin negara tapi sirkel dan sistem nya tidak sehat tapi menghasilkan yg bisa di nikmati oleh anak dan cucu kita berabad-abad kedepan. Apa patut kita akan memvonis ataupun menghujat nya di masa depan. Sama kaya era suharto manfaat nya adalah kita punya bahasa nasional untuk orang2 negara ini dr beda suku beda adat beda budaya dan para pendatang jg mau nggk mau mengikuti kebiasaan warga lokal nya memakai bhs indonesia sebagai bahasa pemersatu di negara ini. Dan yg laen di berikan dr legacy nya suharto adalah toleransi beragama dan penekanan ajaran agama nya. Pendidikan dasar kita di saat kecil memupuk sifat ke nasionalisan kita di era suharto untuk saat ini. Dr mata pelajaran baku bhs indonesia, agama dan pmp (ppkn). Sesederhana itu program nya suharto tp manfaat nya besar tapi miris nya kita melengserkan dengan cara yg tidak hormat. Apa jokowi akan senasib sama suharto ya balik ke kita2 lg nanti nya. Sepatut nya cukup kita mempermasalahkan sistem politik negara kita yg tidak sehat jangan sosok presiden nya. Sama kaya wacana pemberantasan judi ol di sini kita di perlihatkan ketidak mampuan jokowi memberikan mandat usut oknum nya karna dia tau dan terpaksa karna oknum nya bisa kemungkinan dari orang2 parpol nya yg sudah memberikan jalan ke kursi kepresidenan nya. Jokowi jg tidak ada ketegasan sidak kepolisian di saat ini juga dia tidak mau efek kedepan nya makin runyam (bisa jadi kabinet vs parpol, parlement,dan institusi) dipenghujung masa jabatan nya. Tugas kita adalah waktu nya rakyat yg bertindak mengurai sistem kotor perpolitikan negara ini. Di mulai dari kita cari cara agar kepolisian kita saat ini yg lagi banyak ke arogansian nya patut kita yg harus ngoreksi dan mengusut semua kesalahan2 an tiap tindakan instansi satu ini. Penegak hukum lawan nya adalah publik (rakyat). Semoga berita2 saat ini sejalan dengan kemauan publik saat ini membantu membenahi semua yg rusak di sistem negara ini. Jgn memojok kan presiden nya terus.
en_comment:
Ikn if I say is a big blunder of Jokowi from a total of 10 years of his work. 

Will we sentence Jokowi to failure in his work and criticize him in the future? 

I still appreciate Jokowi's work and still consider him the best president in accelerating infrastructure development throughout this country. Let's go back to ourselves if we were in Jokowi's position, becoming a leader of the country but the circle and system are not healthy but produce something that can be enjoyed by our children and grandchildren for centuries to come. Is it right for us to sentence or criticize him in the future. Just like the Suharto era, the benefit is that we have a national language for the people of this country from different tribes, different customs, different cultures and immigrants also want to follow the habits of local residents using Indonesian as a unifying language in this country. And another thing given from Suharto's legacy is religious tolerance and the emphasis on religious teachings. Our basic education when we were little fostered our nationalistic nature in the Suharto era to the present. From the standard subjects of Indonesian language, religion and PMP (PPKN). Suharto's program was that simple but the benefits were great but sadly we overthrew him in a disrespectful manner. Will Jokowi suffer the same fate as Suharto? It's up to us later. We should only question our country's unhealthy political system, not the figure of the president. Just like the discourse on eradicating online gambling, here we are shown Jokowi's inability to give a mandate to investigate the perpetrators because he knows and is forced to because the perpetrators could possibly be from his political party who have paved the way to his presidential seat. Jokowi also has no firmness in conducting a surprise police inspection at this time, he also doesn't want the future effects to be even more complicated (could be cabinet vs political parties, parliament, and institutions) at the end of his term. Our task is the time for the people to act to unravel the dirty political system of this country. Starting from us finding a way so that our current police force, which is currently full of arrogance, should be the ones to correct and investigate all the mistakes of every action of this one agency. The opponent of law enforcement is the public (the people). Hopefully the current news is in line with the current public's wishes to help fix all that is broken in this country's system. Don't keep cornering the president.

comment:
@@ridhoezelo2378 Jangan suka menerawang yg tidak terjadi. Lihat contoh di Jakarta aja, Gubernur punya absolut power apa hasilnya? lebih baik daripada kerja seluruh Gubernur yg ada!

Tapi Jakarta kan kecil ga cocok kalau diterapkan di provinsi lain. Lagipula kerja Gubernur ga dekat dengan rakyat dibawah masih lebih dekat Bupati/Walikota. en_comment:
@@ridhoezelo2378 Don't like to daydream about things that don't happen. Just look at the example in Jakarta, the Governor has absolute power, what are the results? better than the work of all the existing Governors!

But Jakarta is small, it's not suitable if applied in other provinces. Moreover, the Governor's work is not close to the people below, the Regent/Mayor is still closer. So that the mainstay of policy and development should be them.. there is no need for the Governor to hold a large budget. The current budget is not enough and is not even able to regulate the regions below it.

Rather than half-hearted work and power, it is better to just hand it over to the center, so that what is said by the Governor as an extension of the government is real, not just a jargon. So that the people can judge the President's work more fairly and the people also know which party is appointed to blame development in their region: between the President or the Regent/Mayor.

It doesn't make sense for you to bring up Nepotism, Nepotism in the regions is more chaotic because you keep focusing on Jokowi.

author: @Nett.Ragnarok
comment: Menurut saya IKN ini didirikan menuai pro dan kontra, seperti yang kita tahu bahwa kasta tertinggi dalam hukum Indonesia ini adalah hukum viral(bercanda), dari sekian pendapat rakyat Indonesia yang saya teliti satu- persatu di setiap postingan mengenai IKN, saya memeperoleh bahwa IKN ini  memiliki pro dan kontra pada bagian desain, lokasi, dan keindahanya yang justru malah dijadikan bahan lelucon oleh netizen, mulai dari desain yang digadang-gadang mirip garuda dengan kepala menunduk, masyarakat awam yang tidak mengetahui makna dari desain tersebut langsung menghakimi sendiri bahwa desain tersebut buruk, lalu dari keindahan serta kemewahan yang disajikan di IKN malah di jadikan bahan bercandaan seperti "memanjakan para pejabat" dan lain sebagainya. Namun dari yang saya tahu, bahwa IKN didirikan karena penurunan tanah di Jakarta mencapai 2-15 cm per tahun, maka perlu dilakukan tindakan cepat untuk memindahkan ibu kota ke wilayah yang lebih aman
en_comment: In my opinion, the establishment of the IKN has reaped pros and cons, as we know that the highest caste in Indonesian law is the law of viral (jokes), from the opinions of the Indonesian people that I have examined one by one in each post about the IKN, I found that the IKN has pros and cons in terms of design, location, and beauty which have instead been used as jokes by netizens, starting from the design that is said to resemble a garuda with its head bowed, the general public who do not know the meaning of the design immediately judge themselves that the design is bad, then from the beauty and luxury presented in the IKN it has instead been used as jokes such as "spoiling officials" and so on. However, from what I know, the IKN was established because land subsidence in Jakarta reached 2-15 cm per year, so quick action needs to be taken to move the capital city to a safer area

Program pembangunan mercusuar,  yang sangat membanggakan rakyat Indonesia tsb, tentunya nantinya akan membuat negeri ini menjadi lebih dihormati dan lebih disegani oleh dunia Internasional, krn ibarat kita kini memiliki rumah  / tempat tinggal,  mk saat ini kita sudah bisa memiliki rumah yang lebih gagah / lebih megah,  serta dilengkapi dengan berbagai macam fasilitas canggih yg mendukungnya,  dengan  membangun / memasukkan basis berbagai tekhnologi terbaru, yg lebih handal,  untuk mendukung berbagai kegiatan yg ada di wilayah pemerintahan baru kita tsb,  shg para aparat negarapun,  nantinya diharapkan bisa memiliki etos kerja yg tinggi / bisa bekerja lebih tersemangati, setelah nantinya menempati kantor dan tempat tinggalnya yg baru,  yg juga disediakan oleh negara. 
IKN terletak di daerah Kalimantan ( Kalimantan Timur ),  yg mana daerah tsb,  jarang sekali /   bahkan belum pernah terjadi gempa bumi disana,  daerahnyapun belum padat,  malah masih jarang penduduknya ( shg jika roda pusat pemerintah yg baru tsb,  kelak sudah mulai berjalan, mk perpindahan penduduk dari  daerah yg padat penduduknya,  ketempat / daerah yg msh jarang penduduknyapun,  otomatis akan terjadi,  shg terjadi pemerataan penduduk  di Indonesia / terjadi transmigrasi scr otomatis dan dgn adanya hal tsb,  mk persatuan dan kesatuan bangsapun,  akan lebih kokoh / lebih terjalin erat,  termasuk juga hubungan dengan warga pribumi setempat  / warga Dayak, nanti kedepannya akan lebih erat terjalin,  yg pasti pembauran / pernikahan antar suku,  akan lebih cepat terjadi ( krn kelak dgn adanya interaksi sosial / pergaulan diantara mereka,  mk tdk menutup kemungkinan diantara mereka,  kelak akan lebih mudah menyatu dgn adanya proses  pernikahan / perkawinan ), shg hal ini juga akan memperkuat jalinan persatuan dan kesatuan bangsa Indonesia nantinya,  krn perbedaan ras,  sudah tidak lagi menjadi issue penyulut terpecahnya persatuan dan kesatuan bangsa,  krn dgn adanya pernikahan,  berarti telah mempersatukan kedua belah pihak keluarga besar, shg dpt mempercepat dan memperkokoh persatuan dan kesatuan bangsa...... 
IKN terletak diwilayah Kalimantan dan masuk ke dlm wilayah Indonesia bagian tengah,  krn letaknya ditengah -tengah antara Indonesia Barat dan Indonesia Timur,  dengan pusat negara  / ibu kota negara yg berada ditengah -tengah wilayah NKRI tsb,  mk nantinya pembangunanpun akan tersebar lebih merata ke seluruh wilayah Nusantara,  bukan saja pembangunan tsb hanya terkonsentrasi di bagian Indonesia Barat saja ( spt yg selama ini sering kita saksikan bersama ) , namun nantinya pembangunanpun akan tersebar lebih merata,  baik untuk pembangunan diwilayah Indonesia Tengah sendiri  ( di daerah sekitar tempat ibukota yg baru,  termsk juga daerah Sulawesi dsb  ) dan juga pembangunan untuk daerah / wilayah Indonesia bagian Timur,  yg meliputi daerah Papua dan Maluku,  sehingga dengan tersebarnya pembangunan dan hasil -hasil pembangunan,  yg menyebar secara merata diseluruh wilayah NKRI,  mk mempercepat terwujudnya  pembangunan Indonesia yang adil dan merata,  shg antar daerah,  tidak ada lagi terjadi kecemburuan sosial,  apalagi untuk daerah yg memiliki banyak sumber daya alamnya / daerah yg memiliki kekayaan alam yg melimpah, spt daerah Kalimantan dan Papua,  pasti pembangunan didaerah tsb,  nantinya juga akan lebih cepat dilaksanakan, ( shg kecemburuan sosial rakyatnyapun,  terhadap daerah lain dpt ditekan ),  sebab pusat pemerintahan kini telah berada ditengah-tengah wilayah NKRI,  shg pembangunan akan lebih mudah tersebar scr merata,  hingga kepelosok -pelosok negeri,  yg tadinya tdk terjamah sama sekali oleh adanya pembangunan, shg nantinya dgn adanya pemerataan pembangunan diseluruh wilayah NKRI,  mk kehidupan rakyatnyapun akan bisa lebih meningkat dan kemakmuran serta kesejahteraan rakyat dapat segera terwujud,  perpecahan antar bangsapun dapat dicegah ( tak ada lagi daerah  / wilayah yg ingin memisahkan diri dari pemerintahannya,  untuk mendirikan negara merdeka sendiri,  spt adanya gerakan papua merdeka,  dgn adanya pembangunan yg adil dan merata tsb  ),  shg bagi daerah yg memiliki sumber daya alam yg melimpah,  rakyatnyapun juga bisa ikut serta menikmati / merasakan hasil -hasil pembangunan didaerahnya masing -masing, krn dengan adanya pembangunan diwilayahnya tsb, dpt juga meningkatkan pendapatan bagi keluarganya, shg rakyat tak akan mudah lagi untuk diadu domba,  untuk menggulingkan pemerintahannya sendiri,  krn adanya rasa ketdk puasan thd kinerja pemerintah yg kurang memperhatikan pembangunan  di daerahnya  ( spt yg selama ini terjadi,  yaitu pembangunan lebih banyak dikonsentrasikan di wilayah Indonesia bagian Barat saja, yaitu di wilayah Jawa dan Sumatera  ).
Semoga pembangunan IKN yg ada di Kaltim tsb, dapat segera diselesaikan secara tuntas,  meski bpk presiden Jokowi sebentar lagi akan meninggalkan jabatannya sbg presiden / kepala negara.  Semoga bpk Prabowo yg sebentar lagi akan dilantik di kantor Ibu Kota Negara yg baru tsb,  untuk menggantikan bpk Jokowi, beliau / pak Prabowo akan terus ikut mendukung ( dengan sepenuh hati  ) terhadap kelanjutan pembangunan IKN tsb,  hingga nantinya benar -benar tuntas ( mungkin beberapa tahun kedepan,  barulah pembangunan IKN tsb,  akan benar -benar tuntas  ). 
Dengan memiliki gedung pemerintahan baru,  yg dilengkapi dgn berbagai fasilitas canggih sbg sarana pendukungnya, mk in syaa Allah nantinya akan menjadikan negara Indonesia ini menjadi negara yg lebih maju,  lebih terhormat dan lebih bermartabat.  Majulah Negeriku,  Jayalah Bangsaku.......... semoga,  aamiin
en_comment:
The brilliant ideas of President Jokowi are indeed extraordinary, not only building various modern infrastructures in the territory of the Republic of Indonesia, but also including the idea of ​​moving the Capital City of the Republic of Indonesia, from a place/area that is no longer suitable to be maintained as the capital city of a country, to then be moved to a place/area that is more suitable and more supportive of the development process of a country, so that it is hoped that it will later become a Capital City that is suitable and more dignified. The lighthouse construction program, which makes the Indonesian people very proud, will certainly make this country more respected and more respected by the international world, because it is like we now have a house / residence, so now we can have a house that is more dashing / more magnificent, and equipped with various sophisticated facilities that support it, by building / inserting a base of various latest technologies, which are more reliable, to support various activities in our new government area, so that state officials are also expected to have a high work ethic / can work more enthusiastically, after later occupying their new office and residence, which is also provided by the state. The IKN is located in the Kalimantan region (East Kalimantan), which is an area that rarely / has never had an earthquake there, the area is not yet densely populated, in fact it is still sparsely populated (so that if the wheels of the new central government, in the future have started to run, then the movement of people from densely populated areas, to places / areas that are still sparsely populated, will automatically occur, so that there is an even distribution of population in Indonesia / transmigration occurs automatically and with this, the unity and integrity of the nation will be stronger / more closely intertwined, including relations with local indigenous residents / Dayak residents, in the future it will be more closely intertwined, which is certain that inter-ethnic integration / marriage will occur faster (because in the future with social interaction / association between them, it is possible that between them, in the future it will be easier to unite with the process of marriage / marriage), so that this will also strengthen the unity and integrity of the Indonesian nation in the future, because racial differences are no longer an issue that triggers the division of national unity and integrity, because with the marriage, it means that both parties of the extended family have been united, so that it can accelerate and strengthen the unity and integrity of the nation...... 
IKN is located in the Kalimantan region and is included in the central part of Indonesia, because it is located in the middle between West Indonesia and East Indonesia, with the center of the country / capital city in the middle of the territory of the Republic of Indonesia, then later development will be spread more evenly throughout the archipelago, not only is the development only concentrated in the West Indonesia (as we have often witnessed together), but later development will be spread more evenly, both for development in the Central Indonesia region itself (in the area around the new capital city, including the Sulawesi region, etc.) and also development for the regions / regions of Eastern Indonesia, which include the Papua and Maluku regions, so that with the spread of development and development results, which are spread evenly throughout the territory of the Republic of Indonesia, it will accelerate the realization of fair and equitable Indonesian development, so that between regions, there is no more social jealousy, especially for regions that have many natural resources / regions that have wealth abundant nature, such as the areas of Kalimantan and Papua, certainly development in these areas, will also be implemented more quickly, (so that the social jealousy of its people, towards other areas can be suppressed), because the center of government is now in the middle of the territory of the Republic of Indonesia, so that development will be more easily spread evenly, to the remote corners of the country, which were previously untouched by development, so that later with the distribution of development throughout the territory of the Republic of Indonesia, the lives of its people will be able to improve and prosperity and welfare of the people can be realized immediately, divisions between nations can be prevented (there are no more areas / regions that want to separate themselves from their government, to establish their own independent country, such as the Papuan independence movement, with the existence of fair and equitable development), so that for areas that have abundant natural resources, their people can also participate in enjoying / feeling the results of development in their respective regions, because with the development in their region, it can also increase income for their families, so that the people will no longer be easily pitted against each other sheep, to overthrow their own government, because of dissatisfaction with the government's performance which has paid little attention to development in their regions (as has been the case so far, namely that development has been concentrated more in the western part of Indonesia, namely in Java and Sumatra). Hopefully the construction of the IKN in East Kalimantan can be completed soon, even though President Jokowi will soon leave his position as president / head of state. Hopefully, Mr. Prabowo, who will soon be inaugurated in the new National Capital office, to replace Mr. Jokowi, he / Mr. Prabowo will continue to support (wholeheartedly) the continuation of the development of the IKN, until it is truly completed (maybe in the next few years, then the development of the IKN will be truly completed). By having a new government building, which is equipped with various sophisticated facilities as supporting facilities, God willing, it will make Indonesia a more advanced, more honorable and more dignified country. May my country advance, may my nation triumph... hopefully, amen

comment:
@@IwandaA5313  wkwkw salah Indo tiru Amerika yg jadi negara terbaik utk demokrasi dan kapitalis?

Mana ada negara kapitalis demokrasi gak korupsi dan KKN dan berbau feodal?

Trump korupsi malah jadi capres. Negara komunis spt Vietnam dan China berani gantung koruptornya.

Bush Sr angkat Bush Jr lewat pemilu jadi presiden. Hal yg sama dgn JFK angkat anak2nya dan keponakannya jadi anggota Senat lewat pemilu. Bill Clinton nyaris angkat istrinya jadi presiden lewat pemilu.

Amerika barometer demokrasi dan kapitalis dunia. Amerika jadi negara paling kuat di dunia karena demokrasi dan kapitalis.

Lalu salahkan Amin Rais korupsi Rp 200 juta dan angkat 3 anaknya jadi anggota DPR mengikuti Amerika?
Salahkah Megawati angkat anaknya jadi anggota DPR dan ketua MPR lewat pemilu mengikuti Amerika?
Salahkah SBY angkat anaknya jadi anggota DPR lewat mengikuti Amerika?
Salahkah Lee Kuan Yeaw angkat anak2nya jadi PM lewat pemilu mengikuti Amerika?


Lalu kenapa tiba2 jadi salah ketika Jokowi diminta rakyat mengikuati apa yg normal di Amerika?
 
Trump korupsi jadi capres, kenapa Indonesia gak boleh?

Kalau emang gak boleh, siapa suruh Indonesia jadi negara kapitalis demokrasi?

Singapura negara kapitalis demokrasi, Amerika baromater negara kapitalis demokrasi, lalu kenapa Indonesia gak boleh tiru mereka?


Jadi siapapun presiden Indo selama benchmarknya masih Amerika yg suka korupsi dan Nepotisme ya akan tetap korupsi dan nepotisme.
en_comment:
@@IwandaA5313 wkwkw is it wrong for Indonesia to copy America which is the best country for democracy and capitalism? 

Where is there a democratic capitalist country that is not corrupt and has a feudal smell? 

Trump is corrupt but becomes a presidential candidate. Communist countries like Vietnam and China dare to hang their corruptors. 

Bush Sr. appointed Bush Jr. through an election to become president. The same thing happened with JFK appointing his children and nephew as members of the Senate through an election. Bill Clinton almost appointed his wife as president through an election. 

America is the barometer of world democracy and capitalism. America is the strongest country in the world because of democracy and capitalism. 

Then blame Amin Rais for corrupting Rp 200 million and appointing his 3 children as members of the DPR following America? 
Was it wrong for Megawati to appoint her children as members of the DPR and MPR chairman through an election following America? 

Was it wrong for SBY to appoint his children as members of the DPR following America? 

Was it wrong for Lee Kuan Yeaw to appoint his children as PM through an election following America? 

Then why did it suddenly become wrong when Jokowi was asked by the people to follow what is normal in America? 

Trump is corrupt and becomes a presidential candidate, why can't Indonesia? 

If it's not allowed, who told Indonesia to become a capitalist democracy? 

Singapore is a capitalist democracy, America is the barometer of capitalist democracy, then why can't Indonesia imitate them? 

So whoever is the president of Indonesia as long as the benchmark is still America which likes corruption and nepotism, there will still be corruption and nepotism.

author: @InfinixHot-u4b
comment: Bolak balik kan sdh dijelaskan klo ikn itu termasuk pembangunan yg berkelanjutan sampai bbrp tahun kedepan .bukan pembangunan ibukota yg sekali jadi kayak memperbarui peninggalan rumah / gedung tua saja . Ikn dibangun dari awal dasar bahkan hutan belantara . Yg didesain dirancang digarap oleh anak2 bangsa sendiri . Termasuk bahan2 dasar bangunan dll dari hasil karya anak bangsa sendiri . Meski biaya kembang kempis tapi hasil karya tangan 2 anak bangsa sendiri dan untk kepentingan rakyat sendiri . Selain DKI sdh bgtu padat berjubel ramai smua berpusat disitu . Maka agar ada pemerataan kegiatan2 besar menengah maupun bawah ,ibukota memang selayaknya pindah dari luarjawa . Jadi agar apa2 dikit2 semuanya ada dijawa saja kegiatan2 nya . Juga biar ada pemerataan pergerakan ekonomi nya. Bukankah bgtu  sdulur2ku tercinta terbaik sebangsa setanah air . Ya hrs sabarlah step by step tapi dng langkah pasti dan benar . InsyaAllah Allah swt Tuhan yme akan meridhoi tujuan baik kita .Aamin yra .
en_comment: Back and forth it has been explained that IKN is included in sustainable development for the next few years. Not a one-time capital city development like renovating old houses/buildings. IKN is built from scratch, even the wilderness. The design is designed and worked on by the nation's own children. Including basic building materials, etc. from the work of the nation's own children. Although the cost of expansion and contraction is the result of the work of the hands of the nation's own children and for the benefit of the people themselves. In addition, DKI is already so densely packed, crowded, all centered there. So that there is an equal distribution of large, medium and lower activities, the capital city should indeed move from outside Java. So that all the little things are in Java. Also so that there is an equal distribution of economic movement. Isn't that my beloved brothers and sisters, the best in the nation. Yes, you have to be patient, step by step, but with certain and correct steps. God willing, Allah Almighty will bless our good intentions. Amen.

author: @Matjenge
comment: judulnya tidak sesuai dgn penjelasannya. berbicara soal PROGRESS sebaiknya METRO TV. mengambil Data dari Pimpinan Project atau kepala otorita kota Nusantara. yg di maksud 80% itu mungkin Pembangunan PHASE 1 yi; (KIPP) berikut gedung" jalan, dan termasuk CIVIL, ARCHITECT, ELECTRICAL, MECHANICAL, COMUNIKASI, INTERIOR Furniture, kitchen set, FIRE & GAS SYSTEM, PLUMBING, CCTV, DRAINAGE, POTABLE /WASHT WATER, GARDEN, ETC. kalau bicara IKN secara keseluruhan & fasilitasnya dari Phase 1 s/d Phase 5 belum ada kali. BERITA SEPERTI INI LAH yang membuat publik selisih Faham karena karena yg memberitakan TV ternama. tapi tdk menjaga aturan penyiaran. sebaiknya penjelasan baik Vidio maupun Data Hitungan Progress harus di koreksi terlebih dulu baru di publidh ke masyarakat. sukses ya TV metro. jaga Integritasnya itu lebih mantab.
en_comment: the title does not match the explanation. talking about PROGRESS, METRO TV should take data from the Project Leader or the head of the Nusantara city authority. what is meant by 80% is probably the construction of PHASE 1, namely; (KIPP) including buildings, roads, and including CIVIL, ARCHITECT, ELECTRICAL, MECHANICAL, COMMUNICATION, INTERIOR Furniture, kitchen set, FIRE & GAS SYSTEM, PLUMBING, CCTV, DRAINAGE, POTABLE / WASH WATER, GARDEN, ETC. if we talk about the IKN as a whole & its facilities from Phase 1 to Phase 5, there hasn't been any. NEWS LIKE THIS is what makes the public misunderstanding because the one reporting it is a well-known TV. but does not maintain broadcasting regulations. it is better if the explanation of both the Video and the Progress Calculation Data must be corrected first before being published to the public. success, Metro TV. maintaining its integrity is more solid.

author: @MrSukmajati
comment: Swasembada pangan jangan hanya jadi semboyan, seperti apa sih detailnya ? Makanan pokok kita beras, lahan dimana? dan seluas apa? kita punya setelah tanah jawa habis jadi perumahan dan industri, tunjukan. Kalau setengah rakyat indonesia yang makanan pokok beras bisa diganti singkong dan atau sagu saya yakin kita swasembada pangan. Lahan gambut sejuta hektar dikalimantan di era suharto juga contoh usaha swasembada pangan. Bagus utamakan naikan daya beli rakyat sehingga swasembada membeli makanan pokok apapun pilihanya.
en_comment: Food self-sufficiency should not just be a slogan, what are the details? Our staple food is rice, where is the land? and how wide? we have it after Java's land was used up for housing and industry, show it. If half of the Indonesian people whose staple food is rice can be replaced by cassava and/or sago, I am sure we will be self-sufficient in food. The million hectares of peatland in Kalimantan in the Suharto era is also an example of food self-sufficiency efforts. It is good to prioritize increasing people's purchasing power so that they are self-sufficient in buying any staple food of their choice.
